import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['age'], data['height'])
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Height')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between age and height?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['height'])
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_height, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Height')
    plt.ylabel('Values')
    plt.title('What is the average height of people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    age_counts = data['age'].value_counts()
    age_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the most common age in the dataset?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Age Frequency'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.heatmap(data.pivot_table(index='name', columns='age', values='height', aggfunc='count'), cmap='coolwarm', annot=True)
    plt.title("What is the relationship between age and name?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Age")
    plt.ylabel("Name")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
